																		There isn&#039;t nearly enough content about the ethics committee
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrnumbers" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3482376); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3482376&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205757" alt="MrNumbers" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3482376)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrnumbers" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3482376); return false;" >MrNumbers</a></span> <span class="odate time_1512516456 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Dec 2017 23:27</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3646534">
									

<p>So this is part one of a series I'm hoping to do exploring the idea of an SCP ethics committee. If this gets positive reception, I've already got the next one storyboarded and sketched out. Hopefully you guys like this conceptual space as much as I do.</p>
<p>This is my first content on the site. I heard Tales get a lot less coverage than SCPs themselves, but I thought the SCP for this was too weak to make a page for. It would help me out a lot, if you liked it, to share it. God, I feel tacky saying that, but I do mean it.</p>
<p>EDIT: Also, if you're interested in this as well&#8230; I mean, I'd love to eventually be able to make a Hub series out of this.</p>

