															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1414765&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205757" alt="Doctor Cimmerian" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1414765)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;" >Doctor Cimmerian</a></span> <span class="odate time_1512592682 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Dec 2017 20:38</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3647080">
									

<p>What's this, ethics things without Doctor Cimmerian involved? That's crazy! Critique in the collapsible.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Ultimately this isn't interesting for some long stretches, but the parts that click really click well. The &quot;let's stay professional&quot; lines got a bit grating after a while. At first I was fine with it, but it <em>kept happening</em> and at some point a character should either move on or do something besides admonish people.</p>
<p>There's a number of things that get driven home more than once to be honest and it really harms what you're trying to say. Dude vomits 3 times. We got it the first time. We got it the second time. And by the third time it's literally just to structure the joke with the kettle.</p>
<p>Ultimately this feels like a letdown at the end. That's only because a lot of it is very well written and the idea has remarkable potential.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>I already have an idea in my head of the Foundation deciding to start determining the <em>worth</em> of an infant life through anomalous means before doing this sort of killing. Kind of like having your fortune read but you're a baby and if you were gonna end up a Drug Addict they feed you to a monster.</p>
<p>And then a monster isn't satisfied because it wants the babies with better potential&#8230;</p>
<p>Definitely keep working on this. I may end up writing something for this sooner or later (likely involving Cimmerian). If you're interested in having the help of an established site author, PM me.</p>

							</div>

								
