														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3646595">
									

<p>So I'm not really one for the ethics committee usually; focusing on Foundation-funded atrocities is probably one of my least-favorite&#8230;.angles? Is that the right word? Ah well.</p>
<p>That said, this is a really well-written tale. The characters were believable, and their arguments and conclusions made sense given this situation and these choices. Most importantly, for me, at the end of it all they actually came to what I could agree is the least-abhorrent option, instead of settling for some horror-show answer or complacency with the current system. When I do like the ethics committee, I like them doing their jobs right, and this is a great example of that.</p>
<p>So +1 from me, and congrats on your first successful article! Look forward to the rest of this series, if you write it.</p>

