			<div class="content" id="post-content-3646608">
									

<blockquote>
<p>At the end of the day, the Foundation’s gotta eat some babies to save the world. That’s just the facts.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Eh. This basically summarizes my thoughts on the whole thing. These are hardened shadow operatives orchestrating an atrocity in the same manner as at Wannsee; the dialogue, which this entire tale is focused around - it's essentially all one conversation - doesn't reflect that. There's a little gravitas in there but it's overshadowed by gonzo a little too much for my taste. I get that you need the back-and-forth to have color - can't just have everybody be all mrmm hrm casualty reports grumph army group b mumble grumble - but the end result here just doesn't gel with the tone established in that excellently minimal opening graphic.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>There isn't nearly enough content about the ethics committee</p>
</blockquote>
<p>correct, regardless</p>

