    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-3646613">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-3646613">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,3646613)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-3646613">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrnumbers" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3482376); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3482376&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205758" alt="MrNumbers" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3482376)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrnumbers" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3482376); return false;" >MrNumbers</a></span> <span class="odate time_1512528484 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Dec 2017 02:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3646613">
									

<p>Well. Yeah. I didn't want it to be like that though, I wanted to hammer home the fact that it's still very human people who have to orchestrate these decisions, and that <em>sucks</em>.</p>
<p>I feel like cold professionalism would lose a lot of the significance of the situation I was going for. I want the Ethics Committee, in my head, to be the people in the foundation who can't <em>afford</em> to be too hardened, because they're the people whose specific job it is, at the end of the day, to care.</p>
<p>And I feel like if they're all Borges and Strauss, that's a serious problem when the debate isn't something this extreme. But you still need them for when situations like this do occur, so you do get debates like this.</p>

							</div>

								
					
