<p>Yeah, I can appreciate this. I can appreciate this quite a lot.</p>
<p>This might not be how I imagine the Foundation's Ethics Committee running, but it's a version of their proceedings that I can buy into and the details of this horrific magic baby factory farm are on just the right side of 'gratuitously disgusting' for me to buy into. There's a kind of depressingly creative imagination that goes into the affirmative case for 'should we use occult human mass-production to sate the hungers of Keter-class anomalies', and I think that alone is worth a show of appreciation.</p>
<p>Have an upvote. I look forward to seeing what else you do with this iteration of the Committee.</p>

