					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/faustov" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1282427); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1282427&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205758" alt="FaustoV" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1282427)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/faustov" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1282427); return false;" >FaustoV</a></span> <span class="odate time_1512537057 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Dec 2017 05:10</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3646660">
									

<p>first of all, there's a typo there (kdinappings).</p>
<p>Second, I don't know where you got the Julio Borges name, but I swear to God, that just made this even more powerful to me that it was meant originally.</p>
<p>Third, I was reading this, and at the point of the use of commatose women I thought of my wife. I, for a mere second thought of her in this position and horrible realization came to my mind. I honestly considered the implication of this meeting and I found it horrible to no end. I am upvoting this, but it became a bit more personal than your usual eldritch horror tale. I mean, I was already upvoting because I thought it was pretty neat to read a tale expanding onto the Ethics Comittee in this way, but there's a deeper layer for me and it stroke gold.</p>
<p>I'm impressed, disgusted and horrified. +1</p>

